Clustering Methods

Sri Seshadri

K mediods and partion about mediod

The code is from http://www.sthda.com/english/articles/27-partitioning-clustering-essentials/88-k-medoids-essentials/#pam-concept

Standardized USArrests data is used for this exercise. The packages that well be using are cluster and factoextra.

Decision on K

K - Mediods

DBSCAN

#library(factoextra)
data("multishapes")
df <- multishapes[, 1:2]
set.seed(123)
km.res <- kmeans(df, 5, nstart = 25)
fviz_cluster(km.res, df,  geom = "point", 
             ellipse= FALSE, show.clust.cent = FALSE,
             palette = "jco", ggtheme = theme_classic())

dbscan::kNNdistplot(df, k =  7)
abline(h = 0.15, lty = 2)

set.seed(123)
db <- fpc::dbscan(df, eps = 0.15, MinPts = 5)
# Plot DBSCAN results
library("factoextra")
fviz_cluster(db, data = df, stand = FALSE,
             ellipse = FALSE, show.clust.cent = FALSE,
             geom = "point",palette = "jco", ggtheme = theme_classic())
